This has become a staple for quick, delicious soup. I now use the following changes -- pinto beans rather than hominy; sub 2-3 dried whole chipotle peppers, cooked in the soup, for chiles in adobe; added 1/2 a red bell pepper & green bell pepper, diced; 1/2 c frozen corn, and used my own stock, and add 2 lbs of beautiful Maine shrinp, yum. I adjust heat at the end with red pepper flakes. In the summer I add garden tomatoes, and always serve with avocado and lime wedges. Blue corn chips in place of tortilla strips are a colorful touch.

