I made this for the first time for a dinner party and we all thought this soup was awesome. My hubby was still talking about it the next day! I used more chipotle peppers than called for also, and I definately recommend that little squeeze of fresh lime at the table, really brightened the flavor! I've made this soup twice. Once using the golden hominy and once using the white. I have to agree with the other rating, we like it with the white hominy better. The white has a more distictive "mexican" flavor. When making this dish again, I'll use the white. It seems to be easier to find also. The idea of baking the tortilla strips is a good one, I air-dried mine and they seemed a bit chewy. We served with guacamole & chips, Pillsbury cornbread sticks and cold Mexican beer, yum!

